"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"If you just joined crypto and only now catching up with this conversation, choosing between the two chains is pretty easy. Spending roughly $1 instead of more than $100 for the same service is a no-brainer.\\n\\nBut if you’ve been in the Avalanche ecosystem for the past three months, you might still be a bit irked.\\n\\n“Almost \\\\[$2\\\\] for \\\\[a\\\\] small transaction on Pangolin,” [wrote](https://decryptmedia.us17.list-manage.com/track/click?u=cb082838e4bfa8e85cb1b2ac4&id=9abde72cb3&e=728e4331bb) a Redditor back in August when using Pangolin, a decentralized exchange on Avalanche. “Seems like \\\\[no one\\\\] talks about this. Is it just me who \\\\[minds\\\\]? How do you want to make P2E games on this? Will go back to \\\\[a\\\\] lower fees chain prob.\\\"\\n\\nAnother wrote, “I'm very impressed with the speed of this network, but in terms of fees Polygon and Kucoin networks are far far cheaper. I make over 1,000 transactions/week so AVAX in \\\\[its\\\\] current state \\\\[it’s\\\\] just not for me.”\\n\\nSound familiar?\\n\\nIt’s essentially the same conversation the Ethereum community has been having since the network encountered this issue in 2017. And if Avalanche continues to gather more of the market, you can expect to see many of these same issues moving ahead. Sekniqi has himself\",\"timestamp\":1638701562,\"title\":\"a bit irked\"},\"digest\":\"dTWooirURL_uVQbtVbNpehx4NgydIi2l8d0HVendU6U\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x6C8CF69400d769918D3a3Ccb270Cd28255b148Dd\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"LAx_mAXEPbpPbl1sYxrDaIDXs-jyFOK6awq5wyQ5Bvw\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"RGnM2df6IuYMVpdhxHOFj7TsII8d1mQMmnelrArf1QM\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"FyIAdapFtC2INmGboPDgv2XKxPlEMaebSgaV4xLNbzxp-15CVFkD94FSSWx4Ur0o21-Ihd5I4BHWwkcb7pCtKA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x000fc208c277f65ce1fb3669d7f14c972d0100eb6f255d7d33f2b438a56c81b0780c90bcca0c938cee437f8